Today I learned how to archive and compress files in linux using tar and gzip.These commands are commonly used for creating backups and transferring multiple files efficiently.
##commands practiced:
-tar -cvf : create an archive file
-tar -xvf : extract files from an archive
-gzip : Compress a file
-gunzip : decompress a file
-tar -czvf : create and compress an archive
-tar -xzvf :extract a compressed archive
